== Private Communications Policy ==
Please avoid private communications whenever possible. {{project_name_long}} is a Freedom Software project. Free as in Price as well as in Freedom. ([[Why_{{project_name_short}}_is_Freedom_Software|Why?]]) Therefore as many communications as possible should happen in public for transparency. Post in [https://forums.{{project_clearnet}} {{project_name_long}} forums] whenever appropriate and possible.

== Encrypted Communications Policy ==
Encrypted communications are accepted in the following categories: [[Priority Support]], [[Investors]], [[Professional Support]], [[#For Reporting Security Issues|for reporting security issues]], [[#For Private Inquiries|for private inquiries]].

== Social Media ==

There are a few [[Official Online Profiles|{{project_name_long}} Social Media Profiles]], but they should not be relied upon for the latest {{project_name_long}} news. See [[Stay Tuned]] for reliable ways of following {{project_name_long}} news.

In addition, when appropriate {{project_name_long}} developers should be directly contacted by email and not via social media as these are likely to get unnoticed.

Some users may wish to follow or like the available {{project_name_long}} profiles (with an anonymous account). This applies if it is safe to talk about using the {{project_name_long}} platform and you want to share your experience with others. This is also a small way to [[Contribute|contribute]] to the project.

